\begin{note}
Environment variables are another popular way for passing information to a python program.
They are commonly used for passwords, API keys, and other sensative information.
In the shell, they are created with the \lstinline{export} keyword.
There must not be any spaces around the equals sign \lstinline{=}.
In python, the function \lstinline{os.getenv} is used to get the value of an environment variable.
The first parameter is the name of the variable, and the second parameter is a default value to use if the environment variable has not been set.
\end{note}

